text: Mistletoe Corners is an unincorporated community in Columbia County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. The community lends its name to nearby Mistletoe State Park. ==History== A variant name is "Mistletoe". A post office called Mistletoe was established in 1894, and remained in operation until 1916. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Columbia County, Georgia
title: Mistletoe Corners, Georgia
